1. Motivation
Within a GROUPBY, users need to collect per-document data from each group - not just aggregated scalars.
The use cases range from simple ("give me the top-3 titles sorted by rating") to complex ("give me the top-2 full documents per group, sorted by sweetness, including the Redis key and score").

The COLLECT reducer introduces explicit multi-field projection (including whole-document via *, @__key, @__score) and in-group SORTBY/LIMIT.

2. Current State
Today's GROUPBY reducers that retain per-document data:

